commitResults.messageTitle: feat(list): Enhance list command with type filtering
commitResults.messageBody:
The list command now supports an optional type filter to show specific
entry types (e.g., meal, workout, milk, weight). This improves
usability by allowing users to focus on specific data categories.

- Implements a dedicated `ListCommandParser` to handle argument parsing,
  improving modularity and adhering to the Single Responsibility Principle.
- Updates `ListCommand` to accept a `Predicate` for flexible filtering.
- The command defaults to listing all entries if no filter is specified.

commitResults.messageBody:
Refactors the string building logic in the ListCommand's execute method.

The previous implementation, combined with `.trim()`, caused an
off-by-one error in line counts when splitting the output string in the
unit tests.

The new logic constructs the string without a trailing newline, ensuring
consistent output formatting and resolving the test failures.
refactor(command): introduce CommandResult and migrate commands

commitResults.messageTitle: refactor(parser): Improve cohesion with EntryType enum
commitResults.messageBody:
The ListCommandParser was tightly coupled to specific Entry subclasses,
requiring manual updates whenever a new entry type was introduced. This
violated the Open/Closed Principle and made the system brittle.

This commit introduces an `EntryType` enum to act as a single source of
truth for all valid entry types. The parser now relies on this enum
for validation and predicate creation, decoupling it from concrete
implementations.

This change improves cohesion, adheres to OCP, and simplifies future
extensions of the model.
